  levelNumber: 11
  levelName: Altun Ha
  location: Belize District, Belice
  levelDescription: "Where jade gleamed and gods were honored, Altun Ha rose as a
    beacon of Maya power\n\nAltun Ha, \"Rockstone Water\", is a famous Maya city
    in Belize, active from around 250 BC to 900 AD. It was a trade hub linking inland
    routes to the Caribbean coast. The site has two plazas and 13 temples, with the
    Temple of the Masonry Altars as its tallest pyramid.\r\n\r\nArchaeologists discovered
    the Jade Head of the Sun God Kinich Ahau here \u2014 the largest carved jade
    artifact in the Maya world. The city also had clever reservoirs lined with clay
    to store water, showing Maya engineering skill.\r\n\r\nToday, Altun Ha\u2019s
    ruins let us glimpse how the Maya lived, traded, and worshipped, making it one
    of Belize\u2019s most important cultural treasures."
  siteImage: {fileID: 21300000, guid: e3b668bc52d06fd48a9ffa47b6202f68, type: 3}
